20:02.402 --> 20:04.337
but everyone got
something stolen.

20:04.337 --> 20:08.174
Never did catch the bastards
that stole my scooter.

20:08.207 --> 20:09.609
- Uh, scooter?

20:09.676 --> 20:10.743
- Yeah, yeah you know.

20:11.678 --> 20:13.012
- Oh like a moped.

20:13.045 --> 20:14.247
Yeah.
- Oi, oi, oi.

20:14.247 --> 20:17.450
Don't ever call a
scooter a moped.

20:17.517 --> 20:18.951
I'll give you a slap next time.

20:18.951 --> 20:22.889
Anyway, there was one good
thing come out of that night.

20:22.922 --> 20:27.594
See, Sally had the
strangest puppies

20:27.594 --> 20:28.595
that you'd ever seen.

20:36.469 --> 20:37.870
- Puppies, right.

20:46.446 --> 20:49.048
- See, told you
this place was okay.

20:50.883 --> 20:51.651
- I guess.

20:54.921 --> 20:57.256
It's both a beautiful
and a really sad place.

20:58.257 --> 20:59.058
- Sad?

21:00.627 --> 21:02.795
- Looking at it
now, I can imagine

21:02.829 --> 21:04.297
what it once might have been

21:05.765 --> 21:09.536
but then all those years
of neglect and loneliness.

21:11.338 --> 21:13.840
It must have been amazing
when it was full of life.

21:16.909 --> 21:18.778
Now, it just looks
like my grandma,

21:18.845 --> 21:19.912
just hanging in there.

21:21.047 --> 21:22.549
- You do have a way with words.

21:24.050 --> 21:26.486
I could see you becoming
a great novelist one day.

21:28.721 --> 21:30.056
- Yeah?

21:30.089 --> 21:31.991
What sort of books
would I write?

21:33.626 --> 21:34.961
- Romantic ones for sure.

21:35.862 --> 21:37.029
- Really?

21:37.096 --> 21:39.332
You see me as a Mills
& Boons novelist?

21:39.332 --> 21:40.166
- Possibly.

21:41.468 --> 21:43.135
- Am I a graphic novelist?

21:44.203 --> 21:45.705
- I doubt that.

21:45.738 --> 21:48.908
I saw you when Catherine got
that nosebleed last year.

21:48.975 --> 21:50.910
You were hysterical.

21:50.910 --> 21:52.244
- You saw that?

21:52.278 --> 21:53.346
- Uh huh.

21:53.380 --> 21:55.548
She was bawling her eyes out.

21:55.548 --> 21:57.950
- And so the male brain
gets it wrong yet again.

21:57.950 --> 21:59.251
- Hmm?

21:59.251 --> 22:01.621
- I wasn't hysterical
because of the blood.

22:01.654 --> 22:04.123
I was upset for my friend.

22:04.123 --> 22:06.593
She had a date that
night and she got blood

22:06.593 --> 22:07.594
all down her blouse.

22:08.795 --> 22:10.497
It was the one she was
gonna wear on the date.

22:11.798 --> 22:13.600
- I see, okay, so.

22:13.600 --> 22:15.702
It could be graphic novels.

22:17.303 --> 22:19.806
All I know is you've
got a pretty mind.

22:21.674 --> 22:22.675
- Pretty mind?

22:23.910 --> 22:25.912
That could almost be
considered flirting.

22:28.014 --> 22:29.582
- Men don't flirt.

22:29.582 --> 22:33.453
- No, they don't, I agree.

22:33.486 --> 22:35.555
They make it too obvious.

22:37.289 --> 22:38.791
I know exactly why
you've brought me here

22:38.825 --> 22:39.726
and what you want.

22:40.993 --> 22:42.795
- And why is that?

22:42.795 --> 22:44.497
- The question isn't why.

22:44.531 --> 22:46.866
The question is answered
just by my being here.

22:49.368 --> 22:52.204
(woman screaming in distance)

22:52.238 --> 22:53.740
What was that?

22:53.740 --> 22:55.742
- Yeah, I heard that.

22:55.742 --> 22:57.109
- Listen.

22:57.176 --> 22:58.210
(woman sobbing)

22:58.210 --> 22:59.846
- Sounds like crying.

22:59.879 --> 23:02.281
Like a woman crying.

23:02.281 --> 23:04.083
- We should leave.

23:04.083 --> 23:07.720
- No, I want to
see what that is.

23:07.754 --> 23:10.757
(eerie tense music)

23:16.629 --> 23:18.130
- I don't like this.

23:18.130 --> 23:21.133
(ethereal roaring)

23:21.133 --> 23:23.970
That sounded like death itself.

23:24.003 --> 23:27.306
- Whatever it is it sounds
weird and pissed off.

23:27.339 --> 23:29.241
- I think we should leave.

23:29.241 --> 23:32.078
- No, I need to
know what that is.

23:34.046 --> 23:36.916
(ethereal roaring)

23:38.951 --> 23:40.086
- What is it?

23:40.086 --> 23:41.320
- Don't come up here.

23:43.790 --> 23:45.257
- What is it?

23:45.257 --> 23:48.260
(eerie tense music)

23:51.664 --> 23:54.534
(ethereal roaring)

23:57.504 --> 23:58.304
Dan?

24:00.006 --> 24:00.807
Dan.

24:03.009 --> 24:04.010
Dan!

24:04.010 --> 24:05.512
- What?

24:05.545 --> 24:07.780
- Something is watching us.

24:08.915 --> 24:11.918
(eerie tense music)

24:12.885 --> 24:14.887
(wet crunching)

24:14.921 --> 24:15.955
What is that?

24:17.089 --> 24:18.257
- [Dan] I have no idea.

24:19.792 --> 24:20.627
- What do we do?

24:24.631 --> 24:26.933
- Run.

24:26.966 --> 24:27.800
Run.

24:29.301 --> 24:30.336
Run!

24:30.336 --> 24:34.173
(energetic eerie tense music)

24:42.949 --> 24:47.954
(wet crunching)
(Dan screaming)

24:48.420 --> 24:50.089
(gasps)

24:52.759 --> 24:55.762
(eerie tense music)

25:02.501 --> 25:03.670
- Bloody kids.

25:33.465 --> 25:34.934
(alarm ringing)

25:34.934 --> 25:35.735
- Fuck.

25:40.873 --> 25:43.375
(tense music)

25:58.124 --> 26:00.459
- So what we got here, then?

26:02.294 --> 26:04.163
- I can't believe you've
never heard of the film Jaws.

26:04.163 --> 26:06.465
It was a Spielberg masterpiece.

26:06.465 --> 26:08.835
Do you know it took 159
days to make that film

26:08.868 --> 26:10.903
'cause the shark
just wouldn't work.

26:10.970 --> 26:12.639
What films you into, anyway?

