dangerous criminals.

27:09.662 --> 27:11.297
- (mumbles) 'round here.

27:11.297 --> 27:15.334
Anyway, you would of scared
them all away, Ellen.

27:17.236 --> 27:20.639
(tense electronic music)

27:25.945 --> 27:27.279
- It should be okay, now.

27:27.279 --> 27:29.581
Bob has them cornered
in the library.

27:29.581 --> 27:30.582
Come on.

27:42.128 --> 27:43.529
- Hang on.

27:43.529 --> 27:48.534
(alarm ringing)
(tense electronic music)

27:53.672 --> 27:55.341
- Where'd you say they was?

27:55.341 --> 27:56.408
- Library.

27:56.475 --> 27:57.576
- Excuse me, sorry.

27:57.576 --> 27:59.011
Madam, thank you.

28:10.422 --> 28:11.657
- I've got 'em.

28:11.724 --> 28:13.525
I've kept them safe.

28:13.525 --> 28:14.994
They're not gonna go anywhere.

28:14.994 --> 28:16.262
You can count on me.

28:17.163 --> 28:18.530
You can always count on me.

28:18.597 --> 28:20.099
- Nice work, Bob.

28:20.099 --> 28:21.333
- Sir, if you could just put
that weapon down for me, sir.

28:21.333 --> 28:22.334
- Shaun, Shaun.
- Sir, sir.

28:22.334 --> 28:24.136
- It's all right, it's okay.

28:24.170 --> 28:26.005
- I think it's outrageous that
you come onto my property.

28:26.005 --> 28:29.008
- I'll take it from here, Ellen.

28:31.243 --> 28:33.679
Now, I don't recognise yous two.

28:33.712 --> 28:34.613
Names.

28:34.613 --> 28:35.848
- I'm Dan, this is Katie.

28:35.882 --> 28:37.784
- Ah Great Pitchfield
by the looks of em,

28:37.784 --> 28:39.285
I would say.

28:39.285 --> 28:42.054
- Yeah, look like a couple
of wrongens to me, as well.

28:42.088 --> 28:42.922
- [Dan] Did you see it?

28:42.922 --> 28:43.823
- See what?

28:43.823 --> 28:44.957
- The thing in the woods.

28:44.957 --> 28:45.958
- It was chasing us.

28:47.193 --> 28:49.328
- Oh, funny.

28:49.328 --> 28:50.596
Very funny.

28:50.629 --> 28:52.765
Bob is this, Ellen did
you put him up to this?

28:52.765 --> 28:54.600
Is this someones
birthday or something?

28:54.600 --> 28:56.402
- This deadly serious.

28:56.402 --> 28:58.070
- This is fucking serious.

28:58.070 --> 28:59.171
- Excuse me, sir.

28:59.171 --> 29:00.539
Have you or Katie found yourself

29:00.572 --> 29:03.075
taking any illegal
substances today?

29:03.142 --> 29:04.043
- [Dan] No.

29:04.043 --> 29:04.844
- Have you checked the grounds?

29:04.877 --> 29:05.778
It was chasing it.

29:05.778 --> 29:07.279
It attacked Dan.

29:07.279 --> 29:09.715
- This is pathetic.

29:09.715 --> 29:11.117
What attacked you?

29:11.183 --> 29:12.284
- Some thing.

29:12.284 --> 29:13.452
We heard it.

29:13.485 --> 29:15.087
Yeah, we were on the
grounds, we admit that.

29:16.088 --> 29:17.924
We heard a noise in the woods,

29:17.924 --> 29:19.258
we went to investigate it.

29:19.258 --> 29:20.492
- Oh, you don't do that.

29:20.526 --> 29:21.760
- [Dan] What?

29:21.794 --> 29:23.029
- Well, if you've ever
seen any horror film

29:23.029 --> 29:26.498
you know you never
ever investigate.

29:26.498 --> 29:30.803
You get our ass cheeks out
there as soon as possible.

29:30.837 --> 29:32.171
- I agree with Bob.

29:32.171 --> 29:34.340
- Can we please
stick to the facts?

29:35.474 --> 29:36.542
Tell me what happened.

29:37.443 --> 29:40.947
- Uh, well it was,

29:42.348 --> 29:45.184
it was, it was like.

29:46.085 --> 29:47.386
It was like.

29:48.287 --> 29:49.588
- You need to tell them.

29:49.588 --> 29:50.957
- They won't believe us.

29:50.990 --> 29:52.558
- Try us.

29:52.591 --> 29:53.759
- Okay.

29:55.294 --> 29:56.462
It looked like a zombie.

29:58.865 --> 30:01.000
- Oh that wee Billy.

30:01.000 --> 30:02.668
- Probably.

30:02.668 --> 30:05.171
- I think, I think what
they're referring to

30:05.171 --> 30:08.007
is the IC9 reported
to be in the vicinity.

30:08.040 --> 30:10.376
- IC9, is that police
code for zombie?

30:10.376 --> 30:11.510
- No.

30:11.543 --> 30:13.079
It means unknown.

30:13.079 --> 30:15.781
- What I think this is, sir,

30:15.848 --> 30:18.350
is a clearly a case
of mistaken identity.

30:18.384 --> 30:20.286
- We were chased by this thing.

30:20.286 --> 30:21.787
- Are you in charge here?

30:21.820 --> 30:23.322
- [Cooper] And what makes
you say that, little lady?

30:23.389 --> 30:24.823
- You are Police
Sergeant Cooper.

30:24.823 --> 30:26.125
- Oh, you've heard
of me, have you?

30:26.125 --> 30:28.260
- Yeah, my uncle works
in traffic police

30:28.294 --> 30:30.796
and we've heard of you and
this shitty little hamlet.

30:30.796 --> 30:33.099
In Great Pitchfield,
you were voted

30:33.099 --> 30:35.667
the most incompetent sergeant
in the whole district.

30:37.703 --> 30:39.005
- Go that far?

30:39.005 --> 30:40.672
- You need to know
what we understand

30:40.672 --> 30:42.174
what we witnessed here.

30:42.174 --> 30:43.409
- I think you need to
tell us what is going on.

30:43.475 --> 30:45.711
You need to describe
the individual for us.

30:45.711 --> 30:49.115
- Person, they were lying down.

30:49.181 --> 30:51.350
Put it this way, all
their insides, yeah,

30:51.350 --> 30:52.818
they were on the outside.

30:52.885 --> 30:55.821
- Right, you've described
that person as a person,

30:55.821 --> 30:57.756
why not a man or a woman?

30:57.756 --> 30:59.558
- 'Cause it was so mutilated.

30:59.591 --> 31:01.260
I couldn't tell, all right.

31:06.165 --> 31:07.333
- I think we need to
do a perimeter search

31:07.366 --> 31:09.535
and I think we
need to do one now.

31:09.568 --> 31:11.837
- Yeah, I think you're right.

31:11.837 --> 31:13.405
- [Katie] Do you
have any weapons?

31:13.472 --> 31:14.673
- No, we don't carry firearms.

31:14.673 --> 31:16.708
That's a specialist unit does.

31:16.742 --> 31:18.177
- I got weapons.

31:18.210 --> 31:20.846
- You're not really listening
to this drivel, are you?

31:25.884 --> 31:27.486
- So.

31:27.486 --> 31:30.456
- (whispering)

31:30.456 --> 31:33.225
- [Bob] So, what
was the award for?

31:33.259 --> 31:34.460
- What?

31:34.460 --> 31:35.627
- [Bob] Well, the
most incompetent

31:35.661 --> 31:38.030
police sergeant in the district.

31:38.097 --> 31:41.100
(eerie tense music)

31:42.634 --> 31:44.836
(growling)

31:53.745 --> 31:55.247
(gasps)

31:55.281 --> 31:56.782
- What's wrong?

31:56.848 --> 31:59.418
- Whatever it is,
I've just seen it.

32:00.953 --> 32:01.653
- Where?

32:02.621 --> 32:05.457
- It was just staring at me.

32:05.457 --> 32:07.193
Evil eyes.

32:07.259 --> 32:09.595
(eerie tense music)

32:09.595 --> 32:10.929
- Do you need them weapons?

32:11.797 --> 32:13.832
- Weapons.

32:13.832 --> 32:15.034
Yous all stay here.

32:15.101 --> 32:16.969
Bob, we'll talk about
those weapon later.

32:17.003 --> 32:19.305
- I've got tonnes of
them in the greenhouse.

